TITLE: Adding Markers to MarkerClusterGroup in Leaflet
DESCRIPTION: Basic example of creating a marker cluster group, adding markers to it, and adding the group to a map. This demonstrates the fundamental usage pattern of the plugin.
SOURCE: https://github.com/leaflet/leaflet.markercluster/blob/master/README.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
var markers = L.markerClusterGroup();
markers.addLayer(L.marker(getRandomLatLng(map)));
... Add more layers ...
map.addLayer(markers);
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Event Handling in Leaflet MarkerCluster
DESCRIPTION: Example showing how to handle both marker and cluster click events in a MarkerClusterGroup. The code demonstrates setting up event listeners for individual markers and clusters.
SOURCE: https://github.com/leaflet/leaflet.markercluster/blob/master/README.md#2025-04-22_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
markers.on('click', function (a) {
	console.log('marker ' + a.layer);
});

markers.on('clusterclick', function (a) {
	// a.layer is actually a cluster
	console.log('cluster ' + a.layer.getAllChildMarkers().length);
});
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Configuring MarkerClusterGroup Options in Leaflet
DESCRIPTION: Example of creating a marker cluster group with custom configuration options. This shows how to disable default behaviors like spiderfying on max zoom, coverage display on hover, and zoom-to-bounds on click.
SOURCE: https://github.com/leaflet/leaflet.markercluster/blob/master/README.md#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
var markers = L.markerClusterGroup({
	spiderfyOnMaxZoom: false,
	showCoverageOnHover: false,
	zoomToBoundsOnClick: false
});
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Customizing Cluster Icons in Leaflet MarkerClusterGroup
DESCRIPTION: Example of providing a custom iconCreateFunction to customize the appearance of cluster icons. This function receives a MarkerCluster object and returns a divIcon with the count of child markers.
SOURCE: https://github.com/leaflet/leaflet.markercluster/blob/master/README.md#2025-04-22_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
var markers = L.markerClusterGroup({
	iconCreateFunction: function(cluster) {
		return L.divIcon({ html: '<b>' + cluster.getChildCount() + '</b>' });
	}
});
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Updating Marker Icons in Leaflet MarkerCluster
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to update marker icon options and refresh clusters, either for multiple markers or a single marker.
SOURCE: https://github.com/leaflet/leaflet.markercluster/blob/master/README.md#2025-04-22_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
for (i in markersSubArray) {
	markersSubArray[i].refreshIconOptions(newOptionsMappingArray[i]);
}
markers.refreshClusters(markersSubArray);

// If updating only one marker, pass true to
// refresh this marker's parent clusters right away.
myMarker.refreshIconOptions(optionsMap, true);
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Zooming to Cluster Bounds in Leaflet MarkerCluster
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to zoom to the bounds of a cluster when it's clicked, with optional padding configuration.
SOURCE: https://github.com/leaflet/leaflet.markercluster/blob/master/README.md#2025-04-22_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
markers.on('clusterclick', function (a) {
	a.layer.zoomToBounds({padding: [20, 20]});
});
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Handling Cluster Bounds in Leaflet MarkerCluster
DESCRIPTION: Examples of accessing and working with cluster bounds, including getting bounds and convex hull of a cluster.
SOURCE: https://github.com/leaflet/leaflet.markercluster/blob/master/README.md#2025-04-22_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
markers.on('clusterclick', function (a) {
	var latLngBounds = a.layer.getBounds();
});

markers.on('clusterclick', function (a) {
	map.addLayer(L.polygon(a.layer.getConvexHull()));
});
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Getting Visible Parent Marker in Leaflet MarkerCluster
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to get the visible parent of a marker in a MarkerClusterGroup, which could be either the marker itself or its containing cluster.
SOURCE: https://github.com/leaflet/leaflet.markercluster/blob/master/README.md#2025-04-22_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
var visibleOne = markerClusterGroup.getVisibleParent(myMarker);
console.log(visibleOne.getLatLng());
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Customizing Spiderfy Shape Positions in Leaflet MarkerClusterGroup
DESCRIPTION: Example of providing a custom spiderfyShapePositions function to override the default circular spiderfy shape with a linear layout. This function calculates positions for markers when a cluster is spiderfied.
SOURCE: https://github.com/leaflet/leaflet.markercluster/blob/master/README.md#2025-04-22_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
var markers = L.markerClusterGroup({
	spiderfyShapePositions: function(count, centerPt) {
                var distanceFromCenter = 35,
                    markerDistance = 45,
                    lineLength = markerDistance * (count - 1),
                    lineStart = centerPt.y - lineLength / 2,
                    res = [],
                    i;

                res.length = count;

                for (i = count - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
                    res[i] = new Point(centerPt.x + distanceFromCenter, lineStart + markerDistance * i);
                }

                return res;
            }
});
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Refreshing Cluster Icons in Leaflet MarkerCluster
DESCRIPTION: Shows different ways to refresh cluster icons in a MarkerClusterGroup, including refreshing all clusters or specific markers' parent clusters.
SOURCE: https://github.com/leaflet/leaflet.markercluster/blob/master/README.md#2025-04-22_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
markers.refreshClusters();
markers.refreshClusters([myMarker0, myMarker33]);
markers.refreshClusters({id_0: myMarker0, id_any: myMarker33});
markers.refreshClusters(myLayerGroup);
markers.refreshClusters(myMarker);
```

